This is the quick scan. Quick scans are often used when you just want to quickly scan an area and you don\'t want the scan to continue in the background once it finishes. A quick scan does not use fixed areas. They scan wherever the \"preview\" circle is placed

PokeAlert is now able to uncloack Ditto. To achieve this, a Pokemon needs to be caught first (which PokeAlert will do automatically). I advise you to create extra accounts with PokeAlert account generator and use this group of accounts to hunt Ditto. If they start getting CAPTCHAs or get banned, simply re-create a new batch :)

Cache scan is a super fast scan that do not use any of your accounts. Cache scan will display all the Pokemon that ALL the PokeAlert and PokeMesh user have scanned. Sometimes this icon turns red when the cache server is down

In-app Items is a way to reward users when they have donated to the development of PokeAlert. An example of item is \"no advertisements\" which will remove all ads from within the app. (Note that prices are not fixed and you can enter the sum you judge appropriate)

Using the new API will allow you to use more accounts and avoid getting Captcha! To be able to use the new API you will need to enter your \"hash-server key\" which can be bought in this menu. Please understand that PokeAlert is just an affiliate and is NOT the one selling these keys and is NOT the one that has decided to make it not-free)

PokeAlert displays discrete advertisement in the app to financially supports its development. You can also supports PokeAlert by purchasing in-app items such as the no-ads package which will remove all ads form within the app
